// repeaters ka use jo Cables meh ek particular-duri k baad attentuation hota hai usko vapis sahi krne k liyeh.. repeaters ka use hota hai, mtlb repeater weak-signal ko regenerate krta hai , mtlb reapeater uss signal ko uski original/initial value pe laa deta hai. and yehi difference hai between amplifier and repeater ki amplifier toh signal x-times krdeta hai whereas reapeater signal ko uski original/initial value/strength k equal krta hai.

// toh mtlb repeater se apn distance-covered by the signal ko increase kr sktehh hai.
// repeater is a two-port-device mtlb esmeh 2-ports hotehh hai for joiing the 2-cables
// repeater signal ki forwarding krta hai mtlb signal ko rokta nhi hai signal ko aage next-cable meh forward krdeta hai.
// jaise ki repeater ek pure hardware device hai mtlb esmeh koi software nhi hota toh mtlb yeh signal-filtering(mtlb signal ko rokna, tokna , signal ki jach krna etc..etc..) nhi krta. whereas jaise other devices of other osi-layer jaise routers, bridges etc.. voh signal-filterning kr sktehh hai aur krtehh bhi hai.
// reapeater meh signals ki collision hoti hai and maximumly "n" collision ho skti hai, agr cable se "n" devices jude hai toh.
// collision ko apn kam kr sktehh hai by using "Buffer/memory" mtlb agr ek se jada signal saat meh aa rhe hai then apn ek signal ko toh jane denge and other signal ko apne Buffermemory meh store krlenge and then as per vacancy apn unn stored signal ko aage unke path pe chod denge.. but repeater meh esi Buffermemory vali koi cheez nhi hoti.
